    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence data reveals a U.S. military posture characterized by sustained high operational tempo, global power projection, and crisis response capabilities across multiple theaters. The USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) has set a post-Cold War deployment record of 295 days in the Eastern Mediterranean, underscoring a deliberate strategy to maintain persistent carrier presence in a region marked by escalating tensions, including Iran’s blockade of the Strait of Hormuz. Concurrently, the USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) is transiting around the African continent to reinforce U.S. naval forces in the Arabian Sea, demonstrating a strategic flexibility to project power globally while avoiding direct confrontation in contested waters. The commissioning of USS Harvey C. Barnum Jr. (DDG-124) in Norfolk indicates a focus on replenishing destroyer capabilities, though its immediate deployment status remains unclear. In the Eastern Pacific, U.S. forces have conducted 51 strikes on suspected narco boats in five days, reflecting an intensified counter-narcotics mission with significant lethality, raising legal and humanitarian concerns. The presence of multiple ISR and transport aircraft, including USAF MC-12W Liberty and E-3 Sentry platforms, highlights ongoing intelligence gathering and rapid deployment capabilities. Notably, no U.S. Navy amphibious ready groups or submarines are explicitly mentioned in deployed status, suggesting a shift in operational focus toward carrier strike groups and destroyers. The data also indicates potential contingency planning for operations in Cuba, as reported by the Pentagon, alongside North Korea’s recent weapon tests and Iran’s nuclear program developments. Overall, the intelligence points to a U.S. military posture defined by global mobility, high readiness, and a readiness to project power in multiple regions, with particular attention to Iran and counter-narcotics operations in the Eastern Pacific.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
